President Trump delivers remarks in the East Room of the White House to celebrate the passage of the FIRST STEP Act, a bipartisan criminal justice reform bill. The president thanks Vice President Mike Pence and various members of Congress and his administration for their support. He also introduces several individuals who have been released from prison under the FIRST STEP Act and have successfully reintegrated into society. The president emphasizes the importance of second chances and announces plans to focus on successful re-entry and reducing unemployment for Americans with criminal records. He highlights the positive impact of the strong economy on providing opportunities for former inmates. The president concludes by designating April as "Second Chance Month" and expressing his belief in redemption and the potential for all Americans to contribute to society.